WEBVTT

00:01.336 --> 00:03.770
♪ Just call me angel ♪

00:03.772 --> 00:07.807
♪ Of the morning, angel ♪

00:07.809 --> 00:09.542
♪ Just touch my cheek ♪

00:09.544 --> 00:14.125
♪ Before you leave me, baby ♪

00:14.150 --> 00:17.398
♪ Just call me angel of the morn... ♪

00:17.423 --> 00:18.773
♪ Going solo ♪

00:18.798 --> 00:21.665
♪ Wake me up before you go-go ♪

00:21.690 --> 00:28.085
♪ Ah, take me dancing tonight ♪

00:28.640 --> 00:33.443
♪ I want to hit that high ♪

00:33.468 --> 00:35.375
♪ Yeah, yeah ♪

00:35.400 --> 00:38.434
♪ You take the gray
skies out of my way ♪

00:38.459 --> 00:39.882
♪ You make the sun shine brighter... ♪

00:39.906 --> 00:40.914
Hi, Mo.

00:40.939 --> 00:42.375
Morning. Quick question.

00:42.400 --> 00:45.921
Do you always have to play and
sing your music quite that loud?

00:45.946 --> 00:47.846
Well, how else am I
supposed to listen to Wham!?

00:47.871 --> 00:49.392
Their songs demand a certain level

00:49.417 --> 00:50.953
of participation and volume.

00:50.978 --> 00:53.289
It's just that I have a
huge day at work today,

00:53.314 --> 00:54.836
and that sound booming through my walls

00:54.860 --> 00:56.227
wasn't really the best way to start it.

00:56.251 --> 00:57.650
Know what I mean?

00:58.710 --> 01:00.334
Why are you up so early, anyway?

01:00.359 --> 01:01.578
Oh, I didn't go to bed.

01:01.603 --> 01:04.373
At midnight, I had this idea
for a whole line of caftans,

01:04.399 --> 01:05.865
and, you know,
when inspiration strikes...

01:05.867 --> 01:07.901
Hey, what music are you listening to?

01:07.903 --> 01:09.736
I'm happy to take requests
for the next time.

01:09.738 --> 01:11.838
Sorry. You wouldn't know the band.

01:12.054 --> 01:13.673
<i>On today's "Analog Dialogue,"</i>

01:13.675 --> 01:16.031
<i>we have M.I.T. Fellow
and robotics specialist,</i>

01:16.056 --> 01:19.117
<i>Dr. Grace Simmons Hartley,
discussing her...</i>

01:23.184 --> 01:24.695
So, you ready for this?

01:24.720 --> 01:27.430
I think so. I mean,
I do have a pounding headache

01:27.455 --> 01:29.625
and a teeny bit of vomit
in the back of my throat,

01:29.650 --> 01:31.475
- but, like, in a good way.
- Okay.

01:31.500 --> 01:33.435
I just really don't
want to screw this up.

01:33.460 --> 01:36.351
- Next!
- I will have a nonfat latte.

01:36.376 --> 01:38.443
And I'll have a coffee, black.

01:38.726 --> 01:40.771
Keeping it lean for the ladies.

01:40.796 --> 01:43.021
It actually says that
on his dating profile.

01:43.046 --> 01:44.437
It does.

01:44.710 --> 01:46.406
I still don't think it's right for Joan

01:46.408 --> 01:47.969
to force us all to go
after this promotion.

01:47.993 --> 01:50.625
We're not all management material,
and I'm fine with that.

01:50.650 --> 01:52.453
I'm not. I've been a coder long enough.

01:52.478 --> 01:54.553
I need to expand my horizons.

01:54.578 --> 01:55.750
Ooh, that's good.

01:55.775 --> 01:57.282
And then you should tell
her how you crushed it

01:57.306 --> 01:59.235
designing the interface for
our new photo-sharing app.

01:59.259 --> 02:01.598
Except that was really
more of a group effort.

02:01.623 --> 02:03.085
No, it was not a group effort.

02:03.110 --> 02:04.748
It was literally all you.

02:04.773 --> 02:06.593
Now is not the time to be modest.

02:06.595 --> 02:08.595
Joan would be lucky to
have you managing the team,

02:08.620 --> 02:10.764
but you're gonna have to convince her.

02:11.287 --> 02:12.804
Just don't let her rattle you.

02:12.829 --> 02:15.296
Stay confident.
Try to compliment her a little bit,

02:15.321 --> 02:17.406
because let's face it,
the woman's a narcissist.

02:17.431 --> 02:19.718
All very good and thorough advice.

02:21.554 --> 02:23.437
- Hey.
- Howdy.

02:24.410 --> 02:26.718
Did you just say,
"Howdy," to the new guy?

02:26.743 --> 02:29.281
That, I did. I don't know why
we need to keep reliving it.

02:29.306 --> 02:30.726
Why don't you just talk to him?

02:30.751 --> 02:32.437
I'm sure he's perfectly nice.

02:32.462 --> 02:35.390
I'm sure he is, too,
but I have a long history of...

02:35.415 --> 02:37.126
What do you call my past
relationships again?

02:37.150 --> 02:39.336
Unnecessarily complicated,
exhausting for everybody,

02:39.361 --> 02:40.560
the opposite of good.

02:40.562 --> 02:41.960
Yeah, those things.

02:41.985 --> 02:45.326
Which is why, this time,
I'm gonna just take things slow

02:45.351 --> 02:46.537
and wait for the right in.

02:47.092 --> 02:48.092
How does she look?

02:48.117 --> 02:49.469
Good mood or bad mood?

02:49.471 --> 02:51.140
Uh, I'm gonna say all the moods.

02:51.165 --> 02:53.031
Your guess is as good as mine.

02:56.109 --> 02:57.454
Okay.

02:57.479 --> 02:58.978
Okay, look at me.

02:58.980 --> 03:00.780
This is it. Work your magic.

03:00.782 --> 03:02.882
Feel the glory. In it to win it.

03:04.732 --> 03:06.164
I don't know why I'm nervous.

03:06.189 --> 03:08.423
So, Zoey, tell me why you think

03:08.448 --> 03:10.767
you're manager of engineering material.

03:10.792 --> 03:12.492
Great question, Joan.

03:13.243 --> 03:15.454
To start with, I think that I proved
my programming skills

03:15.478 --> 03:17.569
when I helped design the interface
for our photo-sharing app.

03:17.593 --> 03:18.965
Okay, but how much of your work

03:18.967 --> 03:21.187
personally contributed to that project?

03:21.515 --> 03:23.980
- You want, like, a percentage?
- No, I want a latte.

03:24.005 --> 03:25.804
Yes, I want to know how
significant you feel

03:25.829 --> 03:28.623
your contribution was in
terms of the end results.

03:28.648 --> 03:31.398
Well, I mean,
it was definitely a group effort,

03:31.423 --> 03:34.014
but if I had to give
you a concrete number,

03:34.039 --> 03:37.539
I guess I would say... six.

03:37.564 --> 03:38.764
Six?

03:38.789 --> 03:40.156
- ... ty...
- 60?

03:40.181 --> 03:41.905
- ... four?
- 64%?

03:41.930 --> 03:43.129
Correct.

03:45.239 --> 03:46.828
Technical accomplishments aside,

03:46.853 --> 03:48.919
what makes you think you
would be a good manager?

03:48.944 --> 03:50.765
Are you an effective communicator?

03:50.790 --> 03:52.766
Do you think you can get
others to follow your lead?

03:52.790 --> 03:54.976
Are you comfortable being the bad guy?

03:56.202 --> 03:58.373
Well, I'm not really
comfortable with anything.

03:58.398 --> 03:59.882
That's why I became a coder.

04:03.215 --> 04:05.549
But that doesn't mean I
couldn't be a great manager

04:05.574 --> 04:07.382
if given the chance.

04:08.850 --> 04:10.334
What are you typing?

04:10.359 --> 04:11.951
My Pilates instructor.

04:11.953 --> 04:13.656
Can't be late again, Jeff.

04:17.824 --> 04:20.067
Leif, you've been summoned.

04:20.093 --> 04:21.320
How'd you do?

04:21.345 --> 04:24.257
I'm gonna go out on a
limb and say not well.

04:24.282 --> 04:26.776
Really? I thought you two
would be doing each other's nails

04:26.801 --> 04:29.053
and buying matching tote
bags off Etsy in there.

04:29.078 --> 04:31.084
Dude, come on. Not cool.

04:31.109 --> 04:33.443
What? What?

04:33.468 --> 04:34.640
I'm sorry.

04:34.642 --> 04:36.776
Yeah, me, too. I was really hoping

04:36.801 --> 04:39.125
I'd have some good
news to tell my father.

04:53.320 --> 04:56.129
All right, who wants
some freshly delivered,

04:56.131 --> 04:57.986
slightly cold, mediocre pizza?

04:58.011 --> 04:59.398
Mom? Zoey?

04:59.400 --> 05:00.433
Maybe later.

05:00.435 --> 05:02.871
All right. Well, more for me.

05:05.535 --> 05:08.019
Mom, let me take over. You need a break.

05:08.044 --> 05:10.053
No, that's not why we
have you guys here.

05:10.078 --> 05:11.621
We just like the company.

05:11.646 --> 05:14.057
Okay. Well, I can still feed Dad soup.

05:14.082 --> 05:16.048
Yes, but your father doesn't want

05:16.050 --> 05:18.050
to burden you with any of this stuff.

05:20.652 --> 05:22.564
How do you know? He can't speak.

05:22.589 --> 05:23.920
Well, I don't know for sure,

05:23.922 --> 05:26.556
but I have been married
to the man for 40 years,

05:26.558 --> 05:29.299
so I have a pretty good idea.

05:29.324 --> 05:31.252
Can we maybe open a window or something?

05:31.277 --> 05:33.387
Why? You want Dad to catch
a cold on top of everything else?

05:33.411 --> 05:35.409
Yeah, that's exactly
what I want for him.

05:35.434 --> 05:36.599
- Guys.
- He just always loved

05:36.601 --> 05:37.834
being outside, and I don't know.

05:37.836 --> 05:39.002
I thought maybe a little fresh air...

05:39.004 --> 05:40.730
Might give him pneumonia?

05:41.312 --> 05:42.886
He's fine, Zoey.

05:46.886 --> 05:49.182
What's the matter, sweetie? You okay?

05:49.207 --> 05:51.514
Yeah, I've just been getting headaches

05:51.516 --> 05:53.783
and maybe a little bit
of eye pain lately.

05:53.785 --> 05:55.371
I'm sure it's nothing.

05:55.566 --> 05:57.033
Oh, so you're not thinking

05:57.058 --> 05:59.432
that you have what your father has?

05:59.457 --> 06:01.863
I mean, it might have crossed
my mind once or twice.

06:01.888 --> 06:04.504
He didn't show symptoms
until about a year ago,

06:04.529 --> 06:06.596
and it started with balance issues

06:06.598 --> 06:09.418
and speech problems,
not stress headaches.

06:09.443 --> 06:12.410
But, if you're really worried,
go see a doctor, and get an MRI.

06:12.435 --> 06:14.548
No way.
You know how claustrophobic I am.

06:14.573 --> 06:16.106
Well, so is your father,

06:16.108 --> 06:19.506
and he's had seven since January.

06:19.531 --> 06:22.066
Three more,
we get a set of steak knives.

06:24.254 --> 06:26.054
They're not that scary.

06:29.334 --> 06:31.761
Are you sure this isn't
an elaborate teleportation device

06:31.786 --> 06:33.754
that's going to take me
to some parallel universe?

06:33.779 --> 06:35.502
Depends. Where do you want to go?

06:35.527 --> 06:39.261
Um, I'm gonna vote
for anywhere but here.

06:40.943 --> 06:42.809
Uh, now, you're gonna hear some banging,

06:42.833 --> 06:44.832
uh, but you can listen
to music if you like.

06:44.857 --> 06:46.636
We've got Spotify, Pandora,

06:46.661 --> 06:48.589
Apple Music, Google Play.

06:48.614 --> 06:50.447
Doesn't matter. Play anything.

06:50.472 --> 06:52.299
I just want to get this over with.

06:52.324 --> 06:53.690
Here we go.

06:57.172 --> 07:00.604
♪ That's great, it starts
with an earthquake... ♪

07:00.629 --> 07:02.682
Uh, oh.

07:02.707 --> 07:04.120
Mm, I think I was hoping

07:04.122 --> 07:06.182
for something a little
bit more relaxing.

07:06.207 --> 07:08.725
♪ Eye of a hurricane,
listen to yourself churn ♪

07:08.727 --> 07:10.111
♪ World serves its own needs... ♪

07:10.136 --> 07:12.127
Do you have anything that's not as...

07:16.238 --> 07:18.254
Oh, God, an earthquake.

07:18.761 --> 07:21.500
Is this supposed to be happening?!

07:24.232 --> 07:25.932
♪ R-E-S-P-E-C-T ♪

07:25.957 --> 07:27.677
♪ We're not gonna take it ♪

07:27.679 --> 07:29.371
♪ I'm sexy, and I know it ♪

07:29.396 --> 07:30.762
♪ Copacabana ♪

07:30.787 --> 07:32.459
